Review Text: A very nice little spot in Guelph.  The food is excellent and you get a pile of food so come hungry!  The service was great, she was very kind and polite.  Much more than I've seen from a sever in a while.  Will be returning again.

I'm surprised I hadn't heard of this place before, despite living in Guelph for 5 years. Lovely little Greek restaurant! Beautiful interior and the food was delicious. I had the mousaka and a Greek Tempest, but also tried the chicken souvlaki. A bit on the pricier side, but it was well worth it.
Always a good meal. Decently priced and not a chain! Love the fact the menu hasn't changed since we started going there years ago. Guelph needs more of these.
It was awesome great staff and great food and service

Best potatoes in town.
You might think to yourself , well what about the other food ? Why is this review just about potatoes.
The food itself is amazing , but order potatoes and you will see why the first thing I said was best potatoes in town. This is 5 out of 5 on the potatoes alone. 

Like words cannot describe how good this is because the English language doesn't have them.

Poor service, despite a large serving staff in a small, cramped environment. The food was sub-par for the prices asked. Two people at our table received only part of their orders, and water was only served when asked for. There was an hour wait between drink orders. I was given an uncleaned plate during the appetizer. One of the worst restaurant experiences I've had.

I've been to Greek diners with better food and service for half the price. Had I thought to ask at the time, I would have asked to comp my meal as It was basically inedible (completely dried out meat, undercooked rice dish, etc.). I only hope that my experience varies greatly from the average.
Delicious breakfast special! Omelette was amazing!!!! Wait staff was excellent!

This has become our go to restaurant in Guelph.  The food is delicious and the service is always prompt and friendly.  Maria and her team make the experience a pleasure.  Excellent job oh and fantastic potatoes!!!!  You gotta eat here!!!!
Lots of vegetarian/vegan options. Nicely cooked food.
Great food and a cozy atmosphere. Very friendly service. A little more expensive than normal but the servings sizes more than make up for it! Recommended

I liked the atmosphere and the extensive menu but found the food itself disappointing. I like my roasted potatoes to be crispy on the outside, the salad was boring, and there was just too much salt - I had to drink so much water all night afterwards!

Four of us had dinner here for the first time last night. Service was very good and the chef will alter the menu such as changing sauces to your own preference. The Lamb chops with shrimp special was delicious and the Bistro penne was exceptionally good. The restaurant is small and the booths make for a quieter relaxing dining experience. You can actually carry on a conversation with your friends unlike many of the popular Guelph rerstaurants. Definately will be back. This place never disappoints from the service to the delicious meals and the lovely decor! The food is always hot, very tasty and plentiful! Make a reservation though as it fills up quickly. Plenty of free parking! Prices are very reasonable also!

Cozy atmosphere with delicious greek food. I really enjoy the breakfast until 2pm on the weekend, try the opa skillet.
Consistently good value. Food is well prepared with generous portions and service is always friendly.

amazing restaurant for both the food and the service!

Very good food, friendly staff. Price is not the best but it worth it. Very good overall.

Okay. Seriously. Do yourself a favour and eat here! Loved it. I visit Guelph 4 or 5 times a year and always try to stop in here. Today's meal was exceptional and delicious!

We have frequently eaten at Cusina Mediterrranean Bistro choosing it over other restaurants for the range of tastey dishes, friendly and rapid service, and pleasant ambiance.  On our latest visit I had the grilled tenderloin and shrimp special, while my wife chose the grilled chicken and sweat corn salad.  Nicely presented, tastey and most definitely excellent value for the cost.  My only complaint would be that the enjoyment of hot food would be enhanced by plating out on heated plates.  For dessert we had carrot cake and baklava- both excellent.
Meals are always very good especially the salads.
Best souvlaki this side of the Danforth!

Great Bistro, we have never been disappointed with our mean. We always take friends when they are visiting from out of town and everyone loves it.  It's great for date night too!
Fast service. Great prices and gourmet food. Nice atmosphere too. Would highly recommend.
Always great food and service.

Three of us went to this restaurant because the pictures looked amazing, and it was so highly rated. Two of our meals were delicious, and the third looked like a child's meal. He ordered veal Parmesan and it was covered with what looked like shredded cheese. Literally just covered in it. The meals didn't look like these photos, but we got two amazing meals out of three, so I'm giving it four stars.

One of Guelph's best restaurants i.m.o.  My sister in law visiting from Japan had never tried Greek food so off we went starting with saganaki (flaming sharp cheese served on a hot skillet).  We shared chicken souvlaki and a Mediterranean calamari that was grilled and served in a fabulous spicy tomato sauce.   Their prices are quite reasonable for "far better than average" dining.  I'd recommend making a reservation.  It's a small place and usually busy.
Thank you all for making our Valentines dinner so special with your great hospitality. Our dinner was absolutely delicious and services was excellent.
Awesome meal
Food was ok not great and over priced for what you get

Exquisite meal as always. We had the Dinner for Two, which is a combination of a variety of their dishes. We thoroughly enjoyed it and still had some to take home. The staff are always lovely, and the price competitive.

Spent a wonderful evening at Cusina. Amazing food and very nice staff. Best Greek restaurant in the area. 10/10, would recommend to anyone who wants an authentic Greek experience.

This is a definite sleeper for the morning crowd. I've only been here for breakfast, but it is outstanding. I had a skillet which was so flavourful and unique, I've been trying to replicate it with no luck! Prices are reasonable and the decor is gorgeous.
